data.text:
Russian Prime Minister Vladimir Putin, foreground , and Belarusian Prime Minister Sergei Sidorsky seen inspecting a customs checkpoint on the Belarusian-Polish border near the town of Brest, 360 km (225 miles) southwest of Minsk, Belarus, Tuesday, March 16, 2010. Putin is in Belarus to take part in a meeting of government officials of the two ex-Soviet neighbours who agreed to form a customs union.(AP Photo/Sergei Grits)
